Me being a druid I know a thing or two about quadkiting(druid style). As Akbah said in his post mana is one of the main focuses in quading. Before you start to REALLY quad kite mobs do a trial run. <br>
A trial run is simple to do. Pull one mob and start quading it using the quadkite spells, get a feel and you will find out wether or not you have sufficient mana for quading the mobs. If things go wrong you only have one mob aggroed and that makes it easier to get away alive.<br>
