<br>
Crushed gems do drop as do chipped. No BP gems have dropped in Cs to my knowledge though, but Ive given away like 8x melee greaves gems.<br>
<br>
when my mana pool was large enough, around 2800 I didnt bother to hit them with a lvl 1 blast to aggro. I just snared them one each (safer) then ran around in circles (again to lazy to use 3rd view although Ive done it that way too) and finally reapplied BoF. Didnt use Atols since it costs more mana and if someone resists Atols when I pulled with BoF they have different running speed.<br>
<br>
Drakes stopped aggroing once I hit lvl 52 unless I quadded straight through them. Yvolcarn and Azurake are still a pain though, Ive tried to solo Yvolcarn but the bugger seems immune to snare.<br>
<br>
Finally, once you hit lvl 51 and can quad with Pillar of frost Spirocs in Timourous deep is actually better. Less hp, 1500-1800 to Wyverns 3000(correct me if Im wrong here bad memmory). Spirocs are harder to pull though, but not impossible <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
the loot is not as phat though, and one cannot bind in TD, so only way to get there is through the boat in oasis. Some spirocs will start to become lightblue at lvl 52, but I made lvl 53 in like 10 hours of quadding at the spiroc tree. I could make 2 quads and still have 20% mana left, thats an amazing xp rate.<br>
<br>
Once I hit lvl 54 there suddenly where no place left to quad for me. 75% of the wyverns in CS are Lightblue and more or less all spirocs are, Raptors in TD still takes pretty much of my mana bar if I solo one. Add that their aggro range is like 300, anyone with a good throwing weapon will see how nasty it is. I will probably try them again once I hit lvl 55, Ive manage to kill 3 at a time but it was a lucky shot.<br>
